🧠 Key Takeaways


Blind SQL Injection relies on response differences, not direct output


Conditional queries (CASE WHEN) are powerful for inference


Automation is essential for efficiency


Multithreading significantly speeds up extraction



🔐 Mitigation (Defensive Perspective)
To prevent such vulnerabilities:


Use prepared statements / parameterized queries


Avoid directly embedding user input into SQL queries


Implement input validation and sanitization


Use ORM frameworks where possible


Apply least privilege on database users



